reviewText: As some of the reviews have pointed out, this isn't perfect. The video was clearly transferred from VHS but the audio is good.  You will hear some great performances on this including the best live performance of Goodbye Stranger I have ever seen, having Roger there to help on that one makes a huge difference. We are also treated to material from Breakfast in America and Famous Last Words. Some German women in the crowd part ways with their tops too. This is an incredibly special concert as it was Roger's last with Supertramp. It also very sad.  Roger announces that as he thanks the German people and then puts a positive spin on it saying that sometimes change is good... but we all know what has happened since.
Title: N/A

reviewText: Quite frequently "live" performances can be a disappointment to fans of singers and groups which use a lot of studio processing on their albums and singles.This is not the case with Barry White. In fact, after playing all his hits over and over again on the radio in the 1970's (as a DJ), I enjoy this DVD a lot MORE than listening to his original studio versions on CD.There's something I can't put into words. He's singing from down deep in his soul. The loose style and vocalizations are BETTER and RICHER than those original "perfect" versions.  The girls are hugging and kissing him as we strolls singing through the audience...and he never misses a beat.With very few legit DVDs of Barry White's concerts, and even fewer that feature Love Unlimited, you'll want this item in your collection.  It's not HD; it's 1975.  It's Barry at his zenith and it's excellent!

reviewText: I A VERY PLEASED TO BE THE FIRST REVIEWER FOR THIS MATERIAL. IN THE ABSENCE OF ANY OTHER OFFICIAL DVD CONCERT MATERIAL FOR SUPERTRAMP, THIS 17 SONG SET IS A REAL GODSEND. SO, WHILE WE WAIT FOR THE "PARIS" RELEASE, HERE IS THE SCOOP...THIS PERFORMANCE BY SUPERTRAMP IN GERMANY SEEMS TO HAVE BEEN A BROADCAST IN 1983 AND RELEASED IN 2009. THE IMAGES WERE CAPTURED ON VIDEO TAPE WHICH ACCOUNTS FOR THE SOFT PICTURE AND SLIGHTLY OVER-SATURATED COLORS. THERE ARE SLIGHT DROPOUTS THROUGHOUT THAT WILL NOT DETRACT FROM YOUR ENJOYMENT OF THIS SHOW...AS THE SUN WAS SETTING, THE PLAYERS ARE BATHED IN A SLIGHT YELLOW TINT THAT GRADUALLY DIMINISHES. ALL THIS IS COMPLETELY FORGIVABLE GIVEN THE FACT THIS SHOW WAS PROBABLY NEVER MEANT FOR COMMERCIAL RELEASE. CONSIDERING THE 26 YEARS THAT HAVE PASSED SINCE, THE VISUALS HOLD UP VERY WELL. IN A COUPLE OF SPOTS THERE ARE ANIMATED IMAGES THAT OVERLAY THE PERFORMANCE WHICH WAS TYPICAL OF THE TIME. THEY ARE OF SHORT DURATION AND ONLY PURISTS WILL BALK (BUT THEN PURISTS WILL FIND A LOT TO CRITICIZE WITH THIS RELEASE). THE EDITING AND CAMERA WORK ARE ALL GOOD.THE DVD BOASTS TWO SOUNDTRACKS...ONE IN PCM STEREO, THE OTHER IN 5.1 SURROUND. THE 5.1 TRACK IS ANEMIC AND LACKS REAL PUNCH...BUT THE STEREO TRACK IS SPOT ON. GREAT HIGHS AND TERRIFIC LOWS THAT ARE FAIRLY TIGHT, NOT AT ALL MUSHY.AS FOR THE PERFORMANCE ITSELF, THE GROUP IS IN TOP FORM. THERE ARE SO MANY STANDOUT NUMBERS IT IS BEST TO SAY THAT YOU'RE IN FOR A REAL TREAT. ALL THE TRACKS ARE PLAYED WITH REAL GUSTO AND ENTHUSIASM. ABOUT HALFWAY THROUGH THE SHOW ROGER HODGSON ANNOUNCES THIS PERFORMANCE TO BE HIS LAST WITH THE GROUP BEFORE LAUNCHING INTO "GIVE A LITTLE BIT". LEAD VOCAL PERFORMANCES ARE SHARED EQUALLY BETWEEN ROGER AND RICHARD DAVIES AND THEY ARE BOTH IN GREAT VOICE. JOHN HELLIWELL IS FAIRLY ANIMATED AND YOU CAN TELL ALL THE PLAYERS ARE WELL REHEARSED AND TIGHT.I DO NOT KNOW WHY THIS RELEASE BECAME UNAVAILABLE SO QUICKLY EXCEPT TO SURMISE THAT IT MAY NOT BE SANCTIONED BY THOSE OFFICIALLY LICENSED TO RELEASE THIS MATERIAL. I RECEIVED MY COPY FROM ARGENTINA (FROM WHERE THIS ORIGINATES) AND I GOT IT VERY REASONABLY. THIS IS AN NTSC RELEASE WITH AN "ALL REGION" CODING.I HIGHLY RECOMMEND THIS PERFORMANCE AND HOPE YOU CAN SCOOP ONE UP BEFORE THEY ARE ALL GONE. HERE IS THE TRACK LISTING FOR THIS 98 MINUTE SHOW:1.  INTRO2.  CRAZY3.  AIN'T NOBODY BUT ME4.  BREAKFAST IN AMERICA5.  BLOOD WELL RIGHT6.  IT'S RAINING AGAIN7.  PUT ON YOUR OLD BROWN SHOES8.  HIDE IN YOUR SHELL9.  WAITING SO LONG10. GIVE A LITTLE BIT11. FROM NOW ON12. THE LOGICAL SONG13. GOODBYE STRANGER14. DREAMER15. RUDY16. FOOL'S OVERTURE17. SCHOOL18. CRIME OF THE CENTURY

reviewText: Well, this is simply a great show and we are lucky to have it captured on videotape. The only song missing that I would have liked to hear is "Long Way Home". But by 1983, perhaps they had played it a zillions times. The video is great as an historic documentary and the sound is quite good for a video transfer. By 1983, Supertramp were certainly at their peak, and this is a great example of how they arrived there. It is great to see talented artists at their best--playing multiple instruments. Great Concert.

reviewText: Surrounded by the media buzz generated by the possible reunion of the band without its former leader, Enrique Bunbury, EMI releases yet another set in an attempt to please collectors and with the obvious intention of milking the Heroes del Silencio cow (and keeping the image of the band fresh as they have done since 1996 when the band decided to split and take separate ways)Recorded live in Koblenz Germany, 'Live in Germany' contains a set list from the 'El camino del exceso' tour from 1993. The concert in general is quite enjoyable and will remind fans who had the opportunity to see the band live on that tour how those were. The band, Boguslavsky, Andreu, Cardiel, Valdivia and Bunbury were in their best moment while presenting 'El espiritu del vino' (the cover of this set even reminisces the artwork from the aforementioned album) and this concert is a perfect example of why the band was so highly regarded and why there were references to the lizard king after seeing Bunbury sing and perform on stage. Six songs from 'El espiritu del vino' are included, five from 'Senderos de traicion' and one from 'El mar no cesa'. The so famous improvs by Enrique are present in 'Decadencia' where Enrique goes from a gospel song such as 'Motherless child' to 'La mala hora' by Radio Futura.Given that this was a televised concert back in 1993, bootleg copies exist ever since from the original broadcast by SWF3. Being this an official release from EMI, it was expected that the quality would be improved over the existing bootlegs. Speaking of the CD version, there are no complaints, the remastering done in 2011 really helped a lot and the band sounds clear and energetic as back in the day.  The CD even includes a bonus track of 'Hace tiempo', which the insert fails to inform what the source is (if it belongs to the same concert or another one)What you get in the DVD is basically a bad quality rip from the broadcasted version of the show, literally. The DVD is pretty much the TV show as it aired back in the year. It starts with Enrique talking about the band in English and then goes into the opening of the show and the broadcasting net logos (a moose?) All the text that was added for the TV broadcast is still there, which means they did not even get to the video source (or perhaps it was not available anymore) The video is presented in 4:3 and overall the quality is awful, all the noise and scratches from whatever source they used are there. The concert will occasionally cut to interviews (all in English) and then some people talking in German, or even fans giving out their opinions. It is important to note that there are no subtitles other than German!The video runs for about 90 minutes. The DVD menu has no setup menu, no subtitles are included other than predefined German subtitles for when Enrique is interviewed in English. Audio is stereo, which makes sense if you consider they did not have the original source material to do a remaster with it. People interested in importing this will be glad to know it is region free (regions 1-6)While the historical value of the concert and especially the video cannot be denied, it is clear EMI did not put a lot of effort into this release, with a possible reunion happening soon it makes sense for them to start reminding people there was once this great band called Heroes del Silencio. Honestly, after watching this I can understand what Enrique Bunbury was talking about when he mentioned he did not approve of this release that  got released anyways (in an interview with Rolling Stone Spain, December 2011)If you are a fan of the band you will be definitely getting this for its historical value, if you are a casual fan or want to get started into their music, I simply cannot recommend this release as is, Heroes del Silencio deserved better... EMI really needs to stop milking this cow... (or at least do it in a respectful manner)
summary: EMI really needs to stop milking this cow...

reviewText: This DVD is the last concert that Rick Davies and Roger Hodgson EVER played together. You may have seen part of it in "The Story So Far". But this is the entire concert. It is a fitting tribute. Such a huge audience. Such a perfectionary performance (as usual for them, back then).
